=== Potential operators ===

==== Poland ====
BAE Systems is offering the AMPV vehicle to fulfil the need for a heavy IFV for the Polish Army. It would be equipped with the [[ZSSW-30]] remote controlled turret.<ref name="Palowski" >{{Cite web |last=Palowski |first=Jakub |date=2025-04-17 |title=New Player in Poland's Armored Programme [DEFENCE24 EXCLUSIVE] |url=https://defence24.com/industry/new-player-in-polands-armored-programme-defence24-exclusive |access-date=2025-04-17 |website=defence24.com |language=pl}}</ref>
The Polish Army is looking for a heavy IFV ('''CBWP''') for its Abrams tank brigades. The other vehicles in competition include the [[General Dynamics Ajax]], the [[Lynx (Rheinmetall armoured fighting vehicle)|Rheinmetall KF-41 Lynx]], the [[Otokar Tulpar]] and the [[AS21 Redback]]. 
Up to 700 vehicles are planned under the '''CBWP''' programme.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-08-21 |title=700 CBWP infantry fighting vehicles for the Polish Army |url=https://meta-defense.fr/en/2023/08/21/vehicules-de-combat-dinfanterie-cbwp/ |access-date=2025-04-17 |website=meta-defense.fr |language=en}}</ref><ref name="Palowski" />

==== Romania ====
Romania is looking for a successor to its Soviet-era [[infantry fighting vehicle]]s.<ref>{{cite web |date=8 April 2023 |title=România va anunța o licitație pentru vehicule grele de luptă pentru infanterie: Trei mari companii se bat pentru contractul de 3 miliarde |url=https://www.defenseromania.ro/romania-va-anunta-o-licitatie-pentru-vehicule-grele-de-lupta-pentru-infanterie-trei-mari-companii-se-bat-pentru-contractul-de-3-miliarde_622081.html |work=DefenseRomania |language=ro}}</ref> A bid for the supply of those vehicles has been opened for 298 vehicles (2 prototypes, 246 for the Phase I to be supplied by 2032, and Phase II, 50 to be supplied later), and with a local production.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Giovanni |date=2023-03-27 |title=Romania Submits €10 Billion Military Upgrade Plan to Parliament |url=https://www.defense-aerospace.com/romania-submits-e10-billion-military-upgrade-plan-to-parliament/ |access-date=2024-04-12 |website=Defense aerospace |language=en-US}}</ref><ref name="Euroatlantica">{{cite AV media |url=https://podcast.srr.ro/RRA/euroatlantica/-s_1-sh_521 |title=Euroatlantica {{!}} Ediția din 14-03-2024 |date=14 March 2024 |language=ro |time=14:59, 22:04 |work=[[Radio România Actualități]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |date=18 May 2023 |title=Ascod "made in Romania": Producția ar avea la bază un precedent de succes. Primele mașini de luptă pot ajunge la Armată în 3 ani de la semnarea contractului |url=https://www.defenseromania.ro/ascod-made-in-romania-productia-ar-avea-la-baza-un-precedent-de-succes-primele-masini-de-lupta-pot-ajunge-la-armata-in-3-ani-de-la-semnarea-contractului_622734.html |work=DefenseRomania |language=ro}}</ref>
The confirmed participants include:
* [[K21#Future development|K21 Redback]] ([[Hanwha Aerospace|Hanwha]])
* [[ASCOD|ASCOD 2]] ([[General Dynamics European Land Systems#Santa Bárbara Sistemas S.A.|GDELS SBS]])
* [[Lynx (Rheinmetall armoured fighting vehicle)|KF41 Lynx]] ([[Rheinmetall]])
BAE Systems requested to participate in the program, with the AMPV Infantry fighting vehicle and the [[Combat Vehicle 90|CV90]].<ref>{{cite web |date=28 April 2024 |title=Se ascut săbiile pentru viitoarea mașină de luptă a Armatei României: CV90 confirmă că intră în competiția unde Redback și-a anunțat deja prezența |url=https://www.defenseromania.ro/se-ascut-sabiile-pentru-viitoarea-masina-de-lupta-a-armatei-romaniei-cv90-confirma-ca-intra-in-competitia-unde-redback-si-a-anuntat-deja-prezenta_628025.html |work=DefenseRomania |language=ro}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-05-24 |title=BSDA 2024: BAE Systems to pitch AMPV, CV90, and Archer to Romania |url=https://www.janes.com/osint-insights/defence-news/land/bsda-2024-bae-systems-to-pitch-ampv-cv90-and-archer-to-romania |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240622163717/https://www.janes.com/osint-insights/defence-news/land/bsda-2024-bae-systems-to-pitch-ampv-cv90-and-archer-to-romania |archive-date=22 June 2024 |access-date=2024-11-13 |website=Default |language=en}}</ref>

